body_html:
Regarding the error message occurring from tflite_convert.

Here is a list of operators for which you will need custom implementations: RandomUniform, Reciprocal, TensorFlowSqrt, TensorFlowSquare, TensorFlowSum, Unpack. Aborted (core dumped)

The list of supported ops are available here. The two recommended solutions are:

  1. Add a custom op as described here.
  2. Only use the ops that are currently supported by TFLite in your model.

Additionally, we currently have limited support for converting RNN models. You noted your model was a CNN+RNN. While we have implemented the RNN ops (e.g. RNN, LSTM, UNIDIRECTIONAL_LSTM...etc) in TensorFlow Lite, there is no easy way to author the ops currently. We're working on it. Stay tuned.

@suharshs Can you comment on the issue with running the model through quantize_graph.

body:
Regarding the error message occurring from `tflite_convert`.

> Here is a list of operators for which you will need custom implementations: RandomUniform, Reciprocal, TensorFlowSqrt, TensorFlowSquare, TensorFlowSum, Unpack. Aborted (core dumped)

The list of supported ops are available [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/tf_ops_compatibility.md). The two recommended solutions are:
1. Add a custom op as described [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/custom_operators.md).
2. Only use the ops that are currently supported by TFLite in your model.

Additionally, we currently have limited support for converting RNN models. You noted your model was a CNN+RNN. While we have implemented the RNN ops (e.g. RNN, LSTM, UNIDIRECTIONAL_LSTM...etc) in TensorFlow Lite, there is no easy way to author the ops currently. We're working on it. Stay tuned. 

@suharshs Can you comment on the issue with running the model through `quantize_graph`.
